Uses of Package
com.noctarius.borabora.spi.query.pipeline

  • Packages that use com.noctarius.borabora.spi.query.pipeline 
    Package Description
    com.noctarius.borabora
    borabora is a CBOR, the Concise Binary Object Representation, skip-scan processor which consists of a generator as well as a parser.
    com.noctarius.borabora.builder
    This package contains the basic builder classes for Parser (ParserBuilder), Query (QueryBuilder) and Writer (WriterBuilder).
    com.noctarius.borabora.spi.query  
    com.noctarius.borabora.spi.query.optimizer
    This package contains the query optimizer SPI, which interface definitions are used to implement a query optimizer or a strategy on how to apply a set of query optimizers to a given query.
    com.noctarius.borabora.spi.query.pipeline
    This package contains all interfaces required to either implement custom QueryStages or complete QueryPipeline implementations together with their according factories and the pipeline flow control VisitResult.
  • Classes in com.noctarius.borabora.spi.query.pipeline used by com.noctarius.borabora 
    Class and Description
    QueryPipeline
    The QueryPipeline interface defines the actual query execution plan designed as an binary tree pipeline.
  • Classes in com.noctarius.borabora.spi.query.pipeline used by com.noctarius.borabora.builder 
    Class and Description
    PipelineStageFactory
    The PipelineStageFactory implementation is responsible for creating and returning PipelineStage instances based on the provided left, right and stage parameters.
    QueryPipelineFactory
    The QueryPipelineFactory implementation is responsible to build a new QueryPipeline after the optimization is executed.
  • Classes in com.noctarius.borabora.spi.query.pipeline used by com.noctarius.borabora.spi.query 
    Class and Description
    PipelineStage
    The PipelineStage interface defines a single point of execution inside a query execution plan.
